Favor scoring.

ObjectStates.Description: Each time the City Marker circles the Prosperity Track, a purple City Disk is placed beneath the City Marker, and this increases the amount of gold available in the Treasury.

ObjectStates.Name: BlockSquare
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onLoad()
    params = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = "+100",
        position       = {0, 1, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 0, 0},
        width          = 1000,
        height         = 500,
        font_size      = 300,
        color          = {1, 1, 1},
        font_color     = {0, 0, 0},
    }

    self.createButton(params)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    if alt_click then
        -- ignore right-clicks for now
        -- in the future, right-click will increment the city marker
        return
    end

    if color == "Green" then
        disc = getObjectFromGUID('fc3802')
    elseif color == "Yellow" then
        disc = getObjectFromGUID('e0fb49')
    elseif color == "Red" then
        disc = getObjectFromGUID('0d8495')
    elseif color == "Blue" then
        disc = getObjectFromGUID('eb4ccb')
    else
        return
    end

    buttons = disc.getButtons()
    if buttons == nil then
        return
    end
    button = buttons[1]

    score = tonumber(button.label)
    if score == nil then
        label = "100"
    elseif score == 100 then
        label = "200"
    else 
        label = ""
    end
    
    disc.editButton({index = 0, label=label})
end
